  "decision_conditions": [
    "CONDITION:  The wall shall be carefully dismantled by hand and all bricks cleaned set aside and kept safe. The rebuilding of the wall shall be carried out using the existing retained bricks. Should any new bricks be required as part of the rebuilding of the wall these shall match the existing brickwork as closely as possible and the brickwork shall be maintained as such thereafter. The pointing shall be carried out using a lime mortar with a ratio no harder than 1:3:9 (cement:lime:sand). Pointing shall be in a hose joint finish, not weather struck. \r\n\r\nREASON:  In order to safeguard the special architectural or historic interest of the heritage asset in accordance with PPS5, policy D24 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002 and policy CS9A and B of the Islington Core Strategy 2011."
